Ajax striker Justin Kluivert has revealed that he would like to play for Barcelona at some stage in his career. Justin Kluivert is currently regarded as one of the top prospects in European football, with the teenager having already scored nine goals from 44 appearances for Ajax Manchester United have been heavily linked with an approach for Kluivert, but the youngster has indicated that his preferred choice would be a switch to Camp Nou, where father Patrick played 257 games between 1998 and 2004. The 18-year-old told Goal: “My dream club? Barcelona. That is my dream club. To follow in my father’s footsteps? Yes. That is my dream club in the end. “I would not mind going elsewhere, but Barcelona is the dream.” The post Ajax Youngster Justin Kluivert Admits Barcelona Is His Dream Club appeared first on 360Nobs.com. Do you have something awesome to share with the world? Click here to share Do you ever have any question about anything you wish to ask and get answer? Click here to ask Follow us on twitter @NigeriaTodayNG Also, Like us on facebook This post was syndicated from 360Nobs.com. Click here to read the full text on the original website.